{
  "info": {
    "name": "API Contract Validator — Full Test Suite",
    "description": "Tests all 5 tasks and all reward scenarios in sequence.\n\nHow the environment works:\n- POST /reset → start a new episode, get spec + payload\n- POST /step → report one violation at a time\n- GET /state → see internal counters (correct, false positives, etc)\n\nReward rules:\n  Correct violation  → +1.0\n  Wrong guess        → -0.3\n  Duplicate report   → -0.1\n  HINT request       → -0.5\n  DONE (all found)   → +0.5 × (found/total) bonus",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:7860",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 — Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET / (server alive?)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Just checking the server is up and responding.",
                  "// Expected: 200 OK with some JSON"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Server is alive (200)', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 — Reset All 5 Tasks",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Reset: find_type_mismatches (Easy)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// TASK: find_type_mismatches",
                  "// Difficulty: Easy",
                  "// Violations: 4 (sampled from pool of 8)",
                  "// What to find: top-level type errors, missing required fields, invalid enums",
                  "// Max Steps: 10"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Reset returns 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "var body = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Task name is correct', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.observation.task_name).to.eql('find_type_mismatches');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Has 4 violations remaining', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.observation.violations_remaining).to.eql(4);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Has api_spec and payload', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.observation.api_spec).to.be.an('object');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.observation.payload).to.be.an('object');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Episode not done yet', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.done).to.eql(false);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Save payload for inspection in Postman console",
                  "console.log('Payload to validate:', JSON.stringify(body.observation.payload, null, 2));",
                  "console.log('Task description:', body.observation.task_description);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"task_name\": \"find_type_mismatches\"}"
